race.comment: KING CZAR (8) resumes for the Stubbs yard and ended his last prep with two strong runs. Jump-outs have him forward enough and he commands plenty of respect fresh. HELLBERG (2) wasn't quite at his best at Wodonga last time but is drawn well and can prove hard to run down. DEEKAYGEEBEE (6) has mixed form but his Wagga placing two back reads well. Capable of better. ROCCO LINI (3) chased gamely into third at Nowra first-up. Strips fitter, gets in well with the claim and should be competitive. ROCCO LINI (3) resumed well enough at Nowra with a placing at this class and distance. Fitter for the run and warrants thought in a small field.
